We do not allow $\gamma\in{\mathcal{A}_{C}(S;P)}$ to have $\gamma(1) \in P$ but we allow $\gamma(1) \in (C\setminus \{*_C\})$. 
By abuse of notations, an element 
$\gamma \in \mathcal{A}_{C}(S;P)$ often means an actual arc $[0,1] \rightarrow S$ representing $\gamma$
and we may call an element of $\mathcal{A}_{C}(S;P)$ simply an \emph{arc}. 
